We recommended that management require the:

a. Municipal Accountant to record purchases of drugs and medicines, medical, dental and laboratory supplies, food supplies, fuel, oil and lubricant supplies and other supplies to the appropriate inventory account and recognize expenses according to the SSMI for the fair presentation of balances in the financial statements;

b.Adopt the Inventory process for the control, monitoring and recording of inventory as prescribed in Sec. 122 of the NGAS Manual Volume 1;

c.The inventory Custodians of each end user/departments to submit the RIS to the GSO or the distribution list of drugs and medicines, medical, dental and laboratory supplies, Agricultural & Marine Supplies, Animal/Zoological Supplies, Food Supplies, Office Supplies, Other Supplies & Materials as acknowledged by the recipient;

Strictly require the weekly SSMI so as to support of the recording of issuances as expense pursuant to Section 121 of NGAS Manual Vol. 1; and

e. Conduct of the physical count of inventory items by type every semester and submit the required Report of the Physical Count of Inventories (RCPI) to the auditor.

